@VesperDreadlow (4/4) As always, we take great care of our guests, providing a safe and secure environment for them to enjoy their cruise vacation. Once again, we apologize for the delays today, and we look forward to providing our guests with an amazing vacation experience.

@VesperDreadlow (3/4) In addition, and unrelated to the guest passing, 19 guests experienced a stomach related illness. This is not atypical as guests may experience these issues on land, at any time.
@VesperDreadlow (2/4) Separately, please note that during the transatlantic voyage to Puerto Rico, a guest unfortunately passed away due to natural causes.

@VesperDreadlow (1/4) During disembarkation and embarkation at the cruise port in Puerto Rico today, terminal infrastructure issues caused boarding delays. We regret and apologize for any inconvenience.
